# 🏆 DevClash 2026 — 5-Member Team Plan & Timeline

> **Date**: April 18 (10:00 AM) → April 19 (10:00 AM), 2026  
> **Scoring**: 80% Functional Correctness + 20% Completeness  
> **Judging**: 3 Rounds — Hour 7, Hour 14, Hour 23

---

## 👥 Role Assignments (5 Members)

| # | Role | Code Name | Primary Responsibility | Secondary Responsibility |
|---|------|-----------|----------------------|------------------------|
| **M1** | 🎯 **Team Lead / Architect** | **Captain** | System design, architecture decisions, task coordination, judging presentations | Core backend logic when free |
| **M2** | ⚙️ **Backend Lead** | **Engine** | Core business logic, data models, primary algorithms, server-side processing | API endpoints |  
| **M3** | 🎨 **Frontend Lead** | **Pixel** | UI components, user flows, forms, data display, client-side validation | UX edge cases |
| **M4** | 🔗 **Integration / API Specialist** | **Bridge** | API design, backend-frontend integration, external service connections, data flow | Database/state management |
| **M5** | 🛡️ **QA / DevOps / Docs Lead** | **Shield** | Testing, deployment, CI/CD, README, demo video, submission materials | Edge case handling, error states |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Every member must deeply understand their own code.** Judges may grill any member. Each person owns and can explain their section completely.

---

## ⏱️ Hour-by-Hour Timeline

### 🟢 PHASE 0: Pre-Start (8:30 AM – 10:00 AM) — All Members

| Time | Activity | Who |
|------|----------|-----|
| 8:30 AM | Arrive, check-in, set up laptops, power, internet | ALL |
| 9:00 AM | Verify dev environments: Node/Python/etc installed, editors ready, extensions loaded | ALL |
| 9:30 AM | Agree on tech stack preferences, communication plan (who sits where, how to sync) | ALL |
| 9:50 AM | Everyone ready, screens open, waiting for problem statement | ALL |

---

### 🔴 PHASE 1: Problem Analysis & Architecture (Hour 0–2 | 10:00 AM – 12:00 PM)

> **Goal**: Understand the problem completely, design the system, divide features

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **10:00–10:30** | Read problem statement 3x. Lead group discussion. Extract EVERY requirement into a checklist | Same — read & discuss | Same — read & discuss | Same — read & discuss | Same — read & discuss. Write down the requirement checklist |
| **10:30–11:00** | Draw **System Design Diagram** (architecture, data flow, components) | Identify core algorithms & data models needed | Identify all UI screens/views needed | Identify all APIs & integrations needed | Create GitHub repo. Set up project boilerplate |
| **11:00–11:30** | Finalize architecture. Assign features to members. Define interfaces between components | Start setting up backend project structure, models | Start setting up frontend project structure, layout | Define API contracts (endpoints, request/response shapes) | Set up `.gitignore`, `README.md` template, folder structure |
| **11:30–12:00** | Review all assignments. Ensure no gaps. Start coding own section | Begin core data model / database schema | Build basic layout shell (nav, main content area, routing) | Set up API layer / routes / middleware | Write initial README with project description, tech stack |

> [!TIP]
> **M1 must have a clean System Design Diagram by hour 2.** Use Excalidraw, draw.io, or a clean hand-drawn diagram. This is reviewed in Round 1.

#### 📋 Gate Check (Hour 2):
- [ ] All requirements listed in a checklist
- [ ] System design diagram drafted
- [ ] Repo created with clean structure
- [ ] All 5 members have assigned feature ownership
- [ ] Basic project scaffold running locally

---

### 🟡 PHASE 2: Core Build — Happy Path (Hour 2–5 | 12:00 PM – 3:00 PM)

> **Goal**: Build the end-to-end happy path. Input → Processing → Output MUST work.

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **12:00–1:00** | Code the most critical feature / core algorithm alongside M2 | Build primary business logic (the main algorithm/processing) | Build the main input screen/form | Build the primary API endpoint connecting frontend ↔ backend | Test M2's core logic manually. Document edge cases found |
| **1:00–2:00** | Continue core feature. Coordinate between M2 and M3 | Continue core logic. Ensure it handles the primary use case | Build the main output/results display screen | Connect frontend forms to backend API | Write setup instructions in README. Test the integration |
| **2:00–2:30** | 🍽️ **LUNCH BREAK** — Eat but also discuss progress, blockers | 🍽️ LUNCH | 🍽️ LUNCH | 🍽️ LUNCH | 🍽️ LUNCH |
| **2:30–3:00** | Polish System Design Diagram for Round 1. Review overall progress | Fix any bugs in core logic | Fix UI issues. Ensure form → submission works | Ensure API returns correct data format | First full end-to-end test. Document results |

#### 📋 Gate Check (Hour 5):
- [ ] Happy path works: User can input → system processes → output displayed
- [ ] System Design Diagram is presentation-ready
- [ ] At least one core feature fully functional
- [ ] Frontend and backend are connected and communicating

---

### 🔴 PHASE 3: Round 1 Prep & Judging (Hour 5–7 | 3:00 PM – 5:00 PM)

> **Goal**: Prepare for and ace Round 1 (System Design + Initial Progress)

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **3:00–4:00** | Prepare Round 1 presentation talking points. Practice explaining the architecture | Build 2nd most important feature | Polish the UI for the core flow (make it presentable) | Add validation to API endpoints | Prepare a quick demo script for Round 1 |
| **4:00–5:00** | **PRESENT TO JUDGES** — System Design + Demo of core flow | Support M1 during judging. Code when not presenting | Support M1 during judging. Code when not presenting | Support M1 during judging. Code when not presenting | Support M1 during judging. Code when not presenting |

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> ### Round 1 Deliverables (Hour 7):
> - ✅ Clean System Design Diagram
> - ✅ Working demo of core flow (happy path)
> - ✅ Clear explanation of architecture and approach
> - ✅ All members can explain their assigned components

---

### 🟡 PHASE 4: Feature Completion Sprint (Hour 7–11 | 5:00 PM – 9:00 PM)

> **Goal**: Implement ALL remaining required features. No feature left behind.

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **5:00–5:30** | ☕ **TEA BREAK** — Debrief Round 1 feedback. Reprioritize if needed | ☕ TEA | ☕ TEA | ☕ TEA | ☕ TEA |
| **5:30–7:00** | Build feature #3 (or assist whoever is behind) | Build feature #2 continued + feature #4 | Build UI for all remaining features | Build APIs for remaining features. Handle data persistence | Test each feature as it's completed. Log all bugs |
| **7:00–8:00** | Code review. Fix integration issues between components | Add edge case handling to core logic (empty inputs, invalid data) | Add client-side validation to all forms | Add error responses to all APIs (400, 404, 500 codes) | Fix bugs from the bug log. Re-test fixed features |
| **8:00–9:00** | Coordinate final feature push. Help whoever is stuck | Complete remaining backend features | Complete remaining frontend views | Complete all remaining integrations | Update README with all features documented |

> 🍽️ **9:00 PM — Dinner Break** (30 min max, stagger if needed)

#### 📋 Gate Check (Hour 11):
- [ ] ALL required features are implemented (even if rough)
- [ ] Every feature has both frontend UI and backend logic
- [ ] Edge cases handled for core flow
- [ ] No major bugs in critical paths
- [ ] README is up-to-date

---

### 🟡 PHASE 5: Hardening & Round 2 Prep (Hour 11–14 | 9:00 PM – 12:00 AM)

> **Goal**: Bulletproof the app. Handle every edge case. Prepare for Round 2.

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **9:30–10:30** | Test the full app as a user. Find and assign bugs | Harden core logic: error handling, boundary conditions, null checks | Add loading states, error messages, empty states to ALL screens | Add request validation, sanitization, rate limiting | Systematic testing: try to BREAK the app. Log every failure |
| **10:30–11:30** | Fix critical bugs. Ensure end-to-end flow works without manual steps | Fix all backend bugs from M5's testing | Fix all frontend bugs. Ensure responsive/usable UI | Fix all API/integration bugs | Re-test all fixed bugs. Regression testing |
| **11:30–12:00** | **Prepare Round 2 demo.** Practice the full walkthrough | Ensure all features pass manual testing | Ensure UI shows correct states for all scenarios | Ensure all data flows correctly end-to-end | Prepare demo data / test accounts for Round 2 |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Round 2 Deliverables (Hour 14 — 12:00 AM):
> - ✅ ALL required features working
> - ✅ Edge cases handled for core flows
> - ✅ End-to-end flow without manual intervention
> - ✅ Stable — no crashes during demo

---

### 🔴 PHASE 6: Round 2 Judging & Night Push (Hour 14–18 | 12:00 AM – 4:00 AM)

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **12:00–1:00 AM** | **PRESENT TO JUDGES** — Full feature demo | Support during judging | Support during judging | Support during judging | Support during judging |
| **1:00–2:00 AM** | Debrief Round 2 feedback. Assign remaining fixes | Fix any issues judges pointed out (backend) | Fix any UI issues judges noticed | Fix any integration/data issues | Start preparing deployment pipeline |
| **2:00–4:00 AM** | **Sleep rotation**: M1 + M3 sleep 2hrs. M2, M4, M5 continue | Polish remaining features. Add comprehensive error handling | 😴 **Sleep** | Handle remaining edge cases. Optimize performance | Deploy to hosting (Vercel/Railway/Render). Test deployed version |

> [!TIP]
> ### 💤 Sleep Rotation Strategy
> **Never let the whole team sleep at once.** Rotate in pairs:
> - **2:00–4:00 AM**: M1 + M3 sleep → M2, M4, M5 work
> - **4:00–6:00 AM**: M2 + M4 sleep → M1, M3, M5 work
> - M5 (Shield) stays up through the night (critical for deployment/testing) — gets a break in the morning

---

### 🟡 PHASE 7: Morning Recovery & Final Build (Hour 18–22 | 4:00 AM – 8:00 AM)

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **4:00–6:00 AM** | Fix final bugs. Review entire codebase for correctness | 😴 **Sleep** | Final UI polish — only if all features work | 😴 **Sleep** | Continue deployment. Test deployed version end-to-end |
| **6:00–7:00 AM** | All hands back. Final integration testing | Wake up. Review and fix any overnight issues | Wake up. Final frontend fixes | Wake up. Final API fixes | M5 can take a 1hr break (6–7 AM) |
| **7:00–8:00 AM** | **CODE FREEZE for features.** Only bug fixes allowed | Bug fixes only. No new features | Bug fixes only. Visual polish only | Bug fixes only. Data integrity checks | Prepare submission materials: demo video script, final README |

#### 📋 Gate Check (Hour 22):
- [ ] All features complete and working
- [ ] Deployed version matches local version
- [ ] No crashes in any flow
- [ ] README has full setup instructions
- [ ] Demo video script ready

---

### 🔴 PHASE 8: Final Sprint & Submission (Hour 22–24 | 8:00 AM – 10:00 AM)

> **Goal**: Submit everything. Present in Round 3. WIN.

| Time | M1 (Captain) | M2 (Engine) | M3 (Pixel) | M4 (Bridge) | M5 (Shield) |
|------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| **8:00–8:30 AM** | Final full walkthrough of the app. List any last-minute critical bugs | Fix ONLY critical bugs (crashes, data loss) | Fix ONLY visual breaks | Verify deployed version works. Push final commits | **Record 3–5 min demo video** as backup |
| **8:30–9:00 AM** | **Prepare Round 3 presentation.** Practice the pitch | Assist M1 with demo prep | Assist with demo visuals | **Submit through official portal** | Finalize README. List ALL AI tools used |
| **9:00–9:30 AM** | **🔴 ROUND 3 — FINAL JUDGING.** Present complete solution | Support during judging. Answer backend questions | Support during judging. Answer frontend questions | Support during judging. Answer integration questions | Support during judging. Answer deployment/testing questions |
| **9:30–10:00 AM** | Verify submission is confirmed on portal. Push any last commits | Verify all code is committed and pushed | Verify deployed demo works | **Double-check submission** on portal | Verify README, video, all materials are submitted |

> [!CAUTION]
> **Submit by 9:30 AM — 30 minutes before the deadline.** Do NOT wait until the last minute. Portal issues, git push failures, or deployment crashes at 9:59 AM = disaster.

