## 🧠 Communication Protocol

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Sync every 2 hours** | Quick 5-min standup: What's done? What's blocked? What's next? |
| **Blockers = IMMEDIATE escalation** | Don't sit stuck for 30+ min. Ask for help NOW. |
| **M1 decides all architecture disputes** | No time for debates. Captain's call is final. |
| **Git discipline** | Commit every 30 min. Use branches if needed. NEVER break main. |
| **AI tool logging** | Everyone notes which AI tools they use (M5 maintains the master list) |

---

## ✅ Final Submission Checklist

- [ ] Project title + one-line description
- [ ] Track selected (Web3 / Others)
- [ ] GitHub repo is public or judges have access
- [ ] README contains:
  - [ ] All technologies listed
  - [ ] ALL AI tools disclosed
  - [ ] Step-by-step setup instructions
- [ ] Working demo available (deployed link OR video)
- [ ] 3–5 minute demo video recorded (backup)
- [ ] Submitted through **official portal** before 9:30 AM
- [ ] All commits timestamped within hackathon window
- [ ] Presentation deck started (5–10 slides, can finish post-hackathon)

---

> **Remember: 80% Functional Correctness + 20% Completeness. Make it WORK first. Make it COMPLETE second. Make it PRETTY last.** 🚀
